[SN]TITLE[SN]
Barclays leads FTSE 100 higher

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
(Open): The FTSE 100 opened higher, with shares in Barclays leading the way after the bank fired chief executive Antony Jenkins.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
Barclays said it wanted to accelerate the pace of change at the bank, and the news sent its shares up more than 3%.
The FTSE 100 rose 16.90 points to 6,449.11.
